---
// privacy.astro
// Privacy Policy page
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="JMJ Cloud privacy policy explaining how we collect, use, and protect your information."
  currentPath="/privacy"
>
  <section class="privacy-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="page-title fade-in fade-in-1">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle fade-in fade-in-2">
        Last updated: January 2025
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="privacy-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-wrapper fade-in fade-in-3">

        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          JMJ Cloud ("we," "our," or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data.
          This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard information when you visit our website
          at jmjcloud.com.
        </p>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>Analytics Data</h3>
        <p>
          When you accept cookies on our website, we collect anonymous analytics data to understand how visitors
          use our site. This helps us improve the user experience. We use the following services:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Microsoft Clarity:</strong> Records anonymized session replays and heatmaps to understand
            user behavior. Clarity automatically masks sensitive content and does not collect personal information.
            <a href="https://clarity.microsoft.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View Clarity's Privacy Policy</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Analytics 4:</strong> Collects aggregated data about page views, traffic sources,
            and user engagement. IP addresses are anonymized.
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View Google's Privacy Policy</a>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Contact Form Data</h3>
        <p>
          When you submit our contact form, we collect:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your name</li>
          <li>Email address</li>
          <li>Company name (optional)</li>
          <li>Message content</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This information is used solely to respond to your inquiry and is not shared with third parties
          or used for marketing purposes without your explicit consent.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Our website uses cookies only after you provide consent through our cookie banner.
          If you decline cookies, no tracking scripts are loaded and no cookies are set beyond
          what is essential for the website to function.
        </p>

        <h3>Cookie Preferences</h3>
        <p>
          Your cookie preference is stored in your browser's local storage. You can change your
          preference at any time by clearing your browser's local storage and refreshing the page,
          which will display the cookie consent banner again.
        </p>

        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Respond to your inquiries and provide customer support</li>
          <li>Analyze website traffic and usage patterns to improve our content</li>
          <li>Identify and fix technical issues</li>
          <li>Understand which services and content are most valuable to visitors</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. Analytics data
          is processed by Microsoft (Clarity) and Google (Analytics) according to their respective
          privacy policies. We do not combine analytics data with personally identifiable information.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          Contact form submissions are retained only as long as necessary to respond to your inquiry
          and for reasonable follow-up. Analytics data is retained according to the default retention
          periods of Microsoft Clarity and Google Analytics.
        </p>

        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Decline cookies:</strong> Use the cookie banner to decline analytics tracking</li>
          <li><strong>Access your data:</strong> Request a copy of any personal data we hold about you</li>
          <li><strong>Delete your data:</strong> Request deletion of your personal data from our systems</li>
          <li><strong>Withdraw consent:</strong> Change your cookie preferences at any time</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>
          Our website is served over HTTPS, ensuring all data transmitted between your browser and
          our servers is encrypted. We do not store sensitive personal information on our servers.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
          Our website may contain links to third-party websites (such as LinkedIn profiles).
          We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external sites. We encourage
          you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.
        </p>

        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our website is not intended for children under 16 years of age. We do not knowingly
          collect personal information from children.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this
          page with an updated revision date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this privacy policy or our data practices, please
          contact us at:
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="mailto:info@jmjcloud.com">info@jmjcloud.com</a>
        </p>
        <p>
          Or use our <a href="/contact">contact form</a>.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-hero {
    padding: var(--space-20) 0 var(--space-12);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .privacy-content {
    padding: var(--space-8) 0 var(--space-16);
  }

  .content-wrapper {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .content-wrapper h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .content-wrapper h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .content-wrapper h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .content-wrapper p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .content-wrapper ul {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
  }

  .content-wrapper li {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .content-wrapper a {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .content-wrapper a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-secondary);
  }

  .content-wrapper strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .privacy-hero {
      padding: var(--space-24) 0 var(--space-16);
    }
  }
</style>
